page.title: 04ECOLOGY
page.content: WHEN TESTED THE SOIL IN THE AREA VARIED FROM BETWEEN PH5.5 AND PH7.5. RHODODENDRONS GROW ABUNDANTLY IN THE WOODS AND MANY OF THE COMMON WILD PLANTS CAN BE FOUND. A SMALL NUMBER OF THE LESS COMMON WILD PLANTS WERE IN EVIDENCE. MOST COMMON WILD ANIMALS ARE PRESENT, BUT ALSO THE RARER; ADDERS, RED, FALLOW, ROE AND MUNTJAC DEER,(IN BOTH COMMISION AND PRIVATE WOODLAND). FOX, BADGER, STOAT AND WEASEL PROVE TO BE VERY COMMON. KESTRELS ARE THE MOST COMMON BIRD OF PREY PRESENT,AND SPARROW HAWKS ARE OCCASIONALLY SEEN.TAWNY AND BARN OWLS ARE VERY FEW IN NUMBER. HERONS ARE OFTEN SEEN, BUT THE MAIN SUMMER VISITORS ARE; SWALLOWS, MARTINS AND SWIFTS.
